I always get enchilladas when I try a new Mexican place because it's a good way to tell if the rest of their food is good. I ordered the 3 chicken enchilladas suiza dinner with beans and rice, but received 2 enchilladas. That's OK though, because they were probably the worst enchilladas I've had and I didn't even finish the 2 I was given. The chicken is in little balls and over-cooked, not to mention the ranchero sauce is so thin it just pooled in the bottom of the box so essentially the whole thing was pretty tasteless (other than the decent beans and rice). They might have had a bad day, but I won't be ordering from here again.

Your average Mexican restaurant. I had just finished a 13 hour shift, and did not want to go home and cook on a Friday night. I pass by here almost everyday, and I had never given it a try. I ordered to carne asada dinner to go. It traveled well, when i got it home the tortillas were not soggy, nor did they fall apart. The onion and the cilantro were fresh, and the meat was diced up small, and did not have very many pieces of fat, if any at all. If they were, they were undetectable. The rice and beans were average fare, the beans having cheese on top of them. I am not fond of having cheese on mine. I could definitely go back there again.
